bug.short_desc: [IOS] Setting the focus to a text field widget does not work like expected, if rendered application is inside an iframe

long_desc.thetext:
TextField widgets are working fine on IOS, too. But if the application is inside an iframe the input field of the widget does not take the focus correctly.
This issue happens since qx 4.0, the 3.5 branch works better, but not even like expected.
3.5 branch does not allow to show native input field menu on long tap, anyway.
Both branches are working perfect if the application is inside the top frame.
Recommend to make TextField widgets in iframes acting like used in top frame.

Created attachment 1339 Example
open source/frame.html to run application inside an iframe.
First input field is a qx widget.
Second one is a native input field.
As I could see the widget still would not be focused correctly inside the iframe, but the native one.
However, native text field menus would not be applied on native input field however.
